00:53:07,360 --> 00:53:13,840
and think hard about the ideas. It was 
Hank's voice. Hank was right, of course.

583
00:53:14,640 --> 00:53:21,200
Then something terrible happened. He thought, 
Is Hank real? He knew that Harriet Shakespeare  

584
00:53:21,200 --> 00:53:27,840
was real because he had seen her on television. 
But was she really his mother? Perhaps Hank was  

585
00:53:27,840 --> 00:53:32,000
only an idea, a wish - the kind of mother 
that he would like to have, instead of Ma.  

586
00:53:33,120 --> 00:53:37,200
Perhaps he was living in a 
dream world. Crazy Philip Doyle.

587
00:53:38,240 --> 00:53:44,320
He was shaking and could not speak. The Woman 
noticed, and came over to put her arms round him.

588
00:53:45,360 --> 00:53:50,800
'What's the matter, Tug? Everything'll 
be all right. After tomorrow.'

589
00:53:51,920 --> 00:53:56,560
Just then Doyle entered the room, 
with a tray. 'What's happening?'  

590
00:53:57,680 --> 00:54:02,160
he asked the Woman coldly. 'What a 
wonderful picture of motherly love!'

591
00:54:03,280 --> 00:54:05,040
'I was just being a little bit kind...'

592
00:54:06,160 --> 00:54:10,400
'And what about the gun? It's on 
the bed, where Philip can reach it.'  

593
00:54:11,440 --> 00:54:18,080
He picked it up. 'That's dangerous.' He stared 
at the Woman - a long, cold, hard stare.  

594
00:54:19,200 --> 00:54:22,080
After a minute she turned 
away, and went out of the room.

595
00:54:23,200 --> 00:54:26,560
Doyle gave the tray to Tug. 'Here's your supper.'

596
00:54:27,600 --> 00:54:32,160
'Thanks,' Tug said. He took the tray 
with hands that were still shaking.

597
00:54:33,200 --> 00:54:33,840
'Thanks - what?'

598
00:54:34,800 --> 00:54:38,960
'Oh.' He had forgotten. 'Thanks, Doyle.'
 
 

599
00:54:40,480 --> 00:54:41,200
9.50 P.M. 

600
00:54:42,400 --> 00:54:46,480
Jinny hurried down the road to the village, 
and saw Keith waiting by the phone box.

601
00:54:47,600 --> 00:54:52,160
'Come on,' he said excitedly. 
'I've got the number.'

602
00:54:52,160 --> 00:54:59,360
The phone rang and rang. At last a voice 
answered. 'What number do you want? Who  

603
00:54:59,360 --> 00:55:05,920
do you want to speak to? What is your 
name? What number are you calling from?'

604
00:55:05,920 --> 00:55:10,880
Jinny answered all these questions. Then 
she asked Keith, 'What's happening?'

