00:55:17,360 --> 00:55:20,640
Then another voice. 'Lucy Mallory here.'

607
00:55:21,680 --> 00:55:26,880
'Please,' said Jinny hurriedly, 'I want to 
speak to Harriet Shakespeare. It's important.  

608
00:55:27,920 --> 00:55:28,800
It's about Liam.'

609
00:55:29,920 --> 00:55:33,840
'Wait a moment.' The woman did not sound friendly.

610
00:55:34,560 --> 00:55:36,000
Then another voice spoke,  

611
00:55:36,000 --> 00:55:40,880
the deep voice that Jinny and Keith had 
heard on the television news. 'Yes?'

612
00:55:42,000 --> 00:55:48,640
'You - you're Harriet Shakespeare?' asked Jinny, 
not sure what to say. 'I - I know where Liam is.'

613
00:55:49,760 --> 00:55:53,360
'Everyone knows where Liam 
is.' The voice was hard.

614
00:55:54,400 --> 00:56:01,840
'But he's not in your house. He's a prisoner, 
in my village. I've seen him. He's...'

615
00:56:02,800 --> 00:56:06,080
'Listen!' Harriet Shakespeare said angrily.  

616
00:56:07,040 --> 00:56:11,520
'You're the fourteenth person who's phoned me 
at Lucy's to tell me crazy stories about Liam!'

617
00:56:12,480 --> 00:56:18,560
'But you must believe me! The police up here 
won't believe me, and we thought, when we saw  

618
00:56:18,560 --> 00:56:24,080
you on television, that you knew something, 
something that you weren't telling anybody -'

619
00:56:24,080 --> 00:56:30,240
'Oh yes? And what do I know?' Suddenly 
her voice was very quiet, and worried.

620
00:56:31,360 --> 00:56:34,480
'That the terrorists are only 
pretending to hold Liam in your house.  

621
00:56:35,600 --> 00:56:37,280
That really he's in a different place.'

622
00:56:38,400 --> 00:56:46,400
'Oh.' She sounded almost thankful, Jinny thought. 
Then the voice became angry again. 'Well,  

623
00:56:46,400 --> 00:56:53,200
you're wrong about that. Now please just forget 
it, and don't ring me again.' The phone went dead.

624
00:56:54,320 --> 00:56:58,960
'Well,' said Jinny unhappily, 'we 
were wrong. She didn't know anything.  

625
00:57:00,080 --> 00:57:03,200
She didn't believe me. And she was awful'

626
00:57:04,240 --> 00:57:09,840
'Never mind, Jinny,' said Keith slowly. 'I 
agree, we were wrong about what she knew.  

627
00:57:10,960 --> 00:57:14,720
But I'm sure that she was hiding 
something. What could it be?'
 
 
 
 

628
00:57:15,840 --> 00:57:16,640
CHAPTER FIVE

629
00:57:17,680 --> 00:57:18,400
ON THE EDGE

630
00:57:19,520 --> 00:57:23,040
DAY TEN - TUESDAY 16TH AUGUST

631
00:57:23,040 --> 00:57:24,000
2.55 A.M.

632
00:57:25,200 --> 00:57:29,600
'Tug!' The Woman was trying to wake him. 'Tug!'

633
00:57:30,640 --> 00:57:34,720
'Ma? What time is it? What's the matter?'

634
00:57:35,760 --> 00:57:37,520
She spoke quietly into his ear.  

635
00:57:38,560 --> 00:57:43,520
'Don't speak so loudly, or you'll wake 
Doyle. The news is on in a moment.'

