00:57:44,640 --> 00:57:50,320
'In the middle of the night?' But Tug took the 
small radio from her and put it near his ear.

637
00:57:51,360 --> 00:57:57,680
'Good morning. This is the news. Police have 
arrested the terrorists who said that they were  

638
00:57:57,680 --> 00:58:03,200
holding Liam Shakespeare at his home in London. 
But when the police entered the house just before  

639
00:58:03,200 --> 00:58:09,520
midnight, Liam himself was not there. One of 
the group is a boy of fifteen, with fair hair,  

640
00:58:09,520 --> 00:58:15,040
who looks like Liam. It is not known why the 
terrorists were pretending to hold Liam prisoner.  

641
00:58:16,000 --> 00:58:18,480
The police are continuing 
to investigate the matter.'

642
00:58:19,440 --> 00:58:22,400
'I don't understand,' said Tug, still half asleep.

643
00:58:23,520 --> 00:58:30,160
She held his hand. 'You're all right. We just 
have to wait, wait until the end of today.'

644
00:58:31,200 --> 00:58:36,360
Today. Tuesday. 'Aren't you going to tell me -'

645
00:58:36,880 --> 00:58:39,200
'No! Go to sleep now!'

646
00:58:40,240 --> 00:58:44,240
But he could not sleep. He had 
so many things to think about.  

647
00:58:45,440 --> 00:58:50,160
Liam Shakespeare had disappeared. So who was Tug?  

648
00:58:50,160 --> 00:58:56,960
He tried to remember the facts that he knew about 
himself. He liked running. He hated bananas...
 
 

649
00:58:59,360 --> 00:59:00,320
6.45 A.M. 

650
00:59:01,520 --> 00:59:07,520
Jinny was getting breakfast ready. She 
hadn't slept all night. She knew that she  

651
00:59:07,520 --> 00:59:14,240
was right about the boy in the cottage. But today 
I won't have time to worry about it! she thought,  

652
00:59:14,240 --> 00:59:19,680
because it's our harvest day, the busiest day of 
the year. All the neighbours were coming to help.

653
00:59:20,880 --> 00:59:27,680
Just then she noticed a car coming up the narrow 
road to the farm. A visitor! On harvest day!  

654
00:59:28,800 --> 00:59:35,120
It was a woman, dressed in an expensive suit, and 
wearing sunglasses. Jinny went out to meet her.

655
00:59:36,080 --> 00:59:38,080
'You're Jinny Slattery,' the woman said.  

656
00:59:39,120 --> 00:59:42,720
Jinny recognized the deep voice that 
she had heard on the phone last night.  

657
00:59:43,920 --> 00:59:50,800
'You gave your name and the number of the village 
phone box, luckily. That's how I found you. I've  

658
00:59:50,800 --> 00:59:55,360
driven all the way from London, and the girl in 
the post office told me where your farm was.'

659
00:59:56,480 --> 01:00:02,000
'But why have you come?' asked Jinny. 
'You didn't believe me last night!'

660
01:00:03,120 --> 01:00:09,120
'Haven't you heard the news? Liam isn't 
at our home in London. I came to find you  

661
01:00:09,120 --> 01:00:15,520
because you're the only person who seems to know 
where he is. You're my only hope! Where is he?  

662
01:00:16,640 --> 01:00:19,920
How can I get him out?' She sounded desperate.

663
01:00:21,120 --> 01:00:23,360
'Look, I can show you the house where he is, but-'

664
01:00:24,880 --> 01:00:31,120
'We must hurry! There isn't much time! We've 
got to get him out by 2 o'clock today!'
 
 

665
01:00:32,720 --> 01:00:37,040
7.15 A.M.
Tug knew that today was different from other days.  

666
01:00:38,160 --> 01:00:42,560
At breakfast, both Doyle and the Woman kept 
their guns on the table by their hands,  

667
01:00:42,560 --> 01:00:45,520
ready for - what? Tug felt afraid.

668
01:00:46,640 --> 01:00:51,520
Doyle stared coldly at Tug. 'Suppose 
that this is the last day of your life.  

669
01:00:52,720 --> 01:00:54,000
What would you like to do most?'

670
01:00:55,720 --> 01:00:59,600
'Doyle!' said the Woman angrily, 
and put her hand on Tug's arm.

671
01:01:00,720 --> 01:01:06,080
Doyle continued. 'If you don't know what you'd 
choose to do on the last day of your life,  

672
01:01:06,080 --> 01:01:08,000
you don't know what's really important to you.  

673
01:01:09,120 --> 01:01:14,400
Forget about parents and other people. Only 
free people know the answer to that question.'

674
01:01:15,520 --> 01:01:18,720
'It's not easy to know what 
you want,' agreed the Woman.  

675
01:01:19,760 --> 01:01:25,760
'Because you need to know who you really are. 
Nothing to do with your family. Just you.'

676
01:01:26,800 --> 01:01:33,280
'You think you're Liam Shakespeare,' Doyle went 
on. 'We say you're Philip Doyle. Without one of  

677
01:01:33,280 --> 01:01:40,080
those names, you're nobody. And you can't answer 
my question, can you? You don't know who you are!'

678
01:01:41,200 --> 01:01:46,960
They were both staring at him, with their wild, 
crazy eyes. Why should I play their games?  

679
01:01:48,080 --> 01:01:53,200
thought Tug. I'm Tug, I like 
running. I hate bananas...

680
01:01:54,320 --> 01:01:56,320
'Yes, I do know who I am,' he said.

681
01:01:57,440 --> 01:02:00,000
Doyle seemed surprised. 'Well?'  

682
01:02:01,120 --> 01:02:05,840
he said. 'If you're so sure, what would 
you do on the last day of your life?'

683
01:02:06,960 --> 01:02:12,080
Tug thought for a moment. He stared out of 
the window at the great rocky ridge which  

684
01:02:12,080 --> 01:02:17,200
stood high against the sky. It looked black 
and frightening in the early morning light.

685
01:02:18,320 --> 01:02:21,360
'What's that long hill called?' he asked.

686
01:02:22,480 --> 01:02:26,720
Doyle smiled. He thought that Tug 
could not answer his question.  

687
01:02:27,920 --> 01:02:33,920
'That's Ashdale Great Edge. And the rock 
at the end is called the Castle Rock.'

688
01:02:33,920 --> 01:02:39,440
'I can tell you what I'd do on the last 
day of my life,' Tug said calmly. 'I'd run,  

689
01:02:39,440 --> 01:02:43,120
all the way along Ashdale Great 
Edge, from this end to Castle Rock.'

690
01:02:44,240 --> 01:02:47,840
'That's a stupid thing to do!' said Doyle.

691
01:02:48,480 --> 01:02:51,920
But I know that's what I want, and 
nobody can take that away from me,  

692
01:02:51,920 --> 01:02:58,800
thought Tug. Then he noticed the Woman looking 
very sadly at him. He had to ask her the question.

693
01:02:59,920 --> 01:03:02,160
'So - is this going to be 
the last day of my life?'

694
01:03:03,200 --> 01:03:05,360
'I think perhaps - not,' Doyle answered.  

695
01:03:06,320 --> 01:03:09,760
'It will be the last day of someone's 
life, but not yours, I think.'
 
 

696
01:03:11,360 --> 01:03:14,000
7.35 A.M.
Around the  

697
01:03:14,000 --> 01:03:19,200
breakfast table sat Jinny, Oz, their parents, 
Harriet, and Keith, who had just arrived.

698
01:03:20,400 --> 01:03:25,520
'So, Mrs Shakespeare,' said Joe Slattery, 'you 
think that your son is staying in the cottage  

699
01:03:25,520 --> 01:03:30,640
with people who are probably terrorists. You 
don't want to go to the police because it'll  

700
01:03:30,640 --> 01:03:36,480
take too much time. And you want us to think of 
a plan to save your son before two o'clock today.  

701
01:03:37,440 --> 01:03:40,480
On harvest day, the most 
important day of the year for us.'

702
01:03:41,680 --> 01:03:45,520
Harriet stared desperately 
at Joe. 'Yes,' she said.

703
01:03:46,560 --> 01:03:52,400
Joe thought for a moment. 'Well, Keith here says 
that one of the Doyles goes to the post office to  

704
01:03:52,400 --> 01:03:59,440
get a newspaper every day. That'll give us about 
twenty minutes. We can send Jinny to the cottage.  

705
01:04:00,480 --> 01:04:06,160
She goes inside, with some excuse or other. 
Then I'll come up with some of the neighbours,  

706
01:04:06,160 --> 01:04:11,840
we'll knock on the door, and pull out the person 
who comes to the door. That way, neither of the  

707
01:04:11,840 --> 01:04:16,720
Doyles will get a chance to use a gun, and 
we can get both Liam and Jinny out safely.'

708
01:04:17,680 --> 01:04:21,440
Nobody spoke for a second. Then Harriet said,  

709
01:04:21,440 --> 01:04:26,800
'Yes, it's a good plan. All 
right, shall we go?' and got up.

710
01:04:28,000 --> 01:04:36,240
'Wait,' said Joe suddenly. 'Now I have a question. 
Why? You want me to forget about my harvest and  

711
01:04:36,240 --> 01:04:42,400
put my daughter in danger. But why today? 
The television reporters are saying that the  

712
01:04:42,400 --> 01:04:49,200
terrorists won't hurt Liam until Friday. That's 
what Keith says. So we don't need to hurry.'

713
01:04:50,320 --> 01:04:54,320
'I've told you, if the terrorists don't 
get what they want by two o'clock today,  

714
01:04:54,320 --> 01:04:57,840
Liam will die.' Harriet stared angrily at Joe.

715
01:04:58,960 --> 01:05:03,360
Keith suddenly said, 'I don't think they're really 
interested in those special homes for children.  

716
01:05:04,400 --> 01:05:06,320
I think they want something more important.'

717
01:05:07,360 --> 01:05:15,040
'You're right,' said Harriet tiredly. 'They've got 
publicity for their ideas now, of course. But - I  

718
01:05:15,040 --> 01:05:19,920
see that I'll have to tell you what they really 
want. They want to do something that people will  

719
01:05:19,920 --> 01:05:25,760
remember for a long time. They want to destroy, 
