side, shouting and banging on the roof of the car.  

752
01:08:24,720 --> 01:08:28,400
The next minute the car turned away 
from the village, and up to the moors.

753
01:08:29,520 --> 01:08:35,280
The car finally stopped high up above 
the valley. 'Get out!' ordered Doyle.  

754
01:08:36,320 --> 01:08:41,600
'Start walking!' They walked up the long ridge 
that Tug had seen from the kitchen window.  

755
01:08:42,720 --> 01:08:46,960
The wind was strong and cold, and they could 
see a long way on both sides of the ridge.

756
01:08:48,080 --> 01:08:55,680
'Stop here!' shouted Doyle. Now we wait for 
visitors!' They did not have to wait long.  

757
01:08:56,640 --> 01:09:00,560
Two cars drove fast up the hill and 
stopped a few hundred metres away.  

758
01:09:01,680 --> 01:09:06,080
Tug saw the men who had been on the road, 
with a boy who was older than him, and - Hank.

759
01:09:07,280 --> 01:09:13,040
'Stay there!' shouted Doyle to them. 
He was holding the girl by her hair,  

760
01:09:13,040 --> 01:09:19,760
and slowly he put his gun to her head. 'If you 
come any nearer, I'll shoot!' Then he smiled at  

761
01:09:19,760 --> 01:09:26,560
Tug and the Woman. 'Sit down, everyone,' he said. 
'We're going to wait and listen to the news.'

762
01:09:27,760 --> 01:09:35,760
Why not? thought Tug. It all seemed like a dream. 
He sat on the grass, staring at the radio.
 
 

763
01:09:37,920 --> 01:09:41,760
2.25 P.M.
This is probably the last wind  

764
01:09:41,760 --> 01:09:47,840
that I'll ever feel, thought Jinny. When they hear 
the news, they'll know that their plan has failed.  

765
01:09:48,480 --> 01:09:53,120
And then they'll shoot us. She could 
see the blue uniforms of policemen  

766
01:09:53,120 --> 01:09:59,760
in the little group of people waiting by the 
cars. Some policemen had guns. But Doyle and  

767
01:09:59,760 --> 01:10:04,080
the Hare-woman were very careful to keep the 
boy and Jinny in front of their own bodies.

768
01:10:05,280 --> 01:10:11,680
'Right,' said Doyle. 'Now let's listen to the 
two-thirty news. We're waiting to hear of some  

769
01:10:11,680 --> 01:10:17,360
important deaths. If those people haven't died, 
you'll know that Harriet Shakespeare chose to  

770
01:10:17,360 --> 01:10:22,400
save their lives, not her son's. Because 
he's less important to her than they are.'

771
01:10:23,440 --> 01:10:30,720
The boy's face went white. It's not true, Jinny 
wanted to say, she loves you! I've seen that!

772
01:10:31,840 --> 01:10:35,520
They listened silently to the news. At the end,  

773
01:10:35,520 --> 01:10:38,640
Doyle turned off the radio 
and said, 'Now, let's talk.'

774
01:10:39,680 --> 01:10:46,080
'What about?' asked the boy in a high, frightened 
voice. 'You're going to kill me, aren't you?'

775
01:10:47,120 --> 01:10:53,280
'Oh, yes,' said Doyle. 'We're going to kill 
you. But you can choose something first.  

776
01:10:54,400 --> 01:10:59,360
Harriet Shakespeare can't be sure that you're Liam 
because she's too far away to see you clearly.  

777
01:11:00,400 --> 01:11:07,120
And if she's not sure, you can't be sure, can 
you? So I'm going to call her over here. She's  

778
01:11:07,120 --> 01:11:13,200
going to walk slowly towards us. Then we can see 
her face when she decides if you are Liam or not.'

779
01:11:14,320 --> 01:11:17,680
'Then you'll shoot me, I suppose ?' said the boy.

780
01:11:18,800 --> 01:11:21,520
'No, I won't. Your mother will.'

781
01:11:22,640 --> 01:11:25,840
Jinny did not understand why the boy 
turned to stare at the Hare-woman.  

782
01:11:27,040 --> 01:11:29,840
'Ma - would you really shoot me?' he said.

783
01:11:30,960 --> 01:11:37,840
Doyle laughed. 'You don't know her very well, do 
you? She killed her own baby twelve years ago.'

784
01:11:38,960 --> 01:11:40,320
Nobody spoke for a moment.

785
01:11:41,520 --> 01:11:46,000
'So,' continued Doyle, 'you can wait for 
Harriet Shakespeare to decide who you are,  

786
01:11:46,000 --> 01:11:50,640
to put you in a box with a name on 
it. Or you can choose for yourself,  

787
01:11:50,640 --> 01:11:54,160
and spend your last moments of life how you want.'

788
01:11:54,160 --> 01:11:57,280
'We're giving you the chance to 
choose,' added the Hare- woman,  

789
01:11:57,280 --> 01:12:00,560
almost gently, ' - to choose who 
you really are, inside yourself.'

790
01:12:01,680 --> 01:12:09,520
Tug tried to think clearly. Oh Hank! What would 
you choose? Suddenly, he could hear her voice  

791
01:12:09,520 --> 01:12:18,160
in his head. Do I have to decide everything 
for you? Decide for yourself! He smiled. Of  

792
01:12:18,160 --> 01:12:24,720
course she was his mother! He knew it now, 
without question. Now it was easy to decide.

793
01:12:25,760 --> 01:12:28,800
He stood up. 'I'm ready,' he said,  

794
01:12:28,800 --> 01:12:32,640
and began to run away from Hank, along 
the ridge towards the Castle Rock.

795
01:12:33,680 --> 01:12:36,880
Jinny stared. Why was he running that way?  

796
01:12:37,920 --> 01:12:43,600
she thought. But the Hare-woman was now lifting 
the gun in her hands, ready to shoot the boy.

797
01:12:44,560 --> 01:12:49,040
'You're crazy!' screamed 
Jinny. 'Don't shoot him-!'

798
01:12:50,560 --> 01:12:54,160
Doyle's hand suddenly 
covered her mouth. 'Hurry up,  

799
01:12:54,160 --> 01:12:57,760
you stupid cow,' he said to the 
Hare-woman, 'or it'll be too late.'

800
01:12:58,880 --> 01:13:04,160
And Jinny could see that the police, the farmers 
and Harriet were beginning to come nearer.  

801
01:13:04,160 --> 01:13:10,720
Jinny stared at the Hare-woman. Her face looked 
desperate, like... who was it? Like Harriet  

802
01:13:10,720 --> 01:13:15,520
Shakespeare, when she arrived at the farmhouse, 
worried about her son, because she loved him.

803
01:13:16,640 --> 01:13:22,720
Suddenly Jinny bit Doyle's hand hard, and pulled 
her mouth away. She shouted at the Hare-woman,  

804
01:13:22,720 --> 01:13:25,040
using the words that her 
own mother had used to her.

805
01:13:26,080 --> 01:13:28,240
'It's because you love him 
that you want to kill him!  

806
01:13:29,280 --> 01:13:31,840
But if you kill him, you'll 
only destroy yourself!'

807
01:13:32,880 --> 01:13:38,320
The Hare-woman looked round, surprised. 
At that moment, there was a bang and she  

808
01:13:38,320 --> 01:13:45,360
put her hand to her side. A policeman had shot 
her. Doyle ran to take her gun before she fell,  

809
01:13:45,360 --> 01:13:51,040
but before he could take it, she threw it high up 
in the air. It fell over the side of the ridge.

810
01:13:52,320 --> 01:13:57,440
'Run, Tug, run! You're free!' 
she called into the wind.

811
01:13:58,480 --> 01:14:01,120
And Harriet Shakespeare, running towards them,  

812
01:14:01,120 --> 01:14:05,360
cried at the same moment, 'Tug, 
it's all right! You're safe!'

813
01:14:06,480 --> 01:14:12,240
Tug heard the sound of the gun, and then the 
two shouts behind him. But he did not stop,  

814
01:14:12,240 --> 01:14:17,600
because the only thing that mattered was the 
running. His legs ached, and his feet hurt, but  

815
01:14:17,600 --> 01:14:23,200
in front of him was the Castle Rock and he knew 
that he could reach it. And as he ran, he sang  

816
01:14:23,200 --> 01:14:32,680
in his head, This is me. Here I am, Hank. Here 
I am, Ma. This is me. This is who I am.
 
 
 
 
 
 

817
01:14:32,680 --> 01:14:34,284
- THE END -

